s are **3x longer** than traditional searches\n- **YouTube ($11.38B, +8.7%):** Missed estimates; FY2025 YouTube (ads + subs) crossed **$60B** annual for the first time\n- YouTube miss was the main concern from the report\n\n---\n\n### 6. AI Commentary (Gemini, AI Overviews, Infrastructure)\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| Gemini App MAUs | 750M+ (up from 650M in Q3) |\n| AI Mode DAUs | 75M |\n| Tokens processed/min | 10B+ |\n| Gemini cost reduction (2025) | -78% serving unit costs |\n| Gemini Enterprise paid seats | 8M+ |\n| Companies using Gemini Enterprise | 2,800+ |\n| Companies using Gemini (any) | 120,000+ |\n\n**Key Pichai quotes:**\n- \"We were able to lower Gemini serving unit costs by 78% over 2025\"\n- \"Gemini 3 Pro has consistently processed three times as many daily tokens as 2.5 Pro\"\n- \"AI continues to drive an expansionary moment\" in search\n- \"I do expect to go through the year in a supply constrained way\"\n\n**Monetization:** CFO Schindler — \"We are in the early stages experimenting with AI mode monetization, like testing ads below [AI] responses\"\n\n---\n\n### 7. Forward Guidance & CapEx\n\n| | Amount |\n|-|--------|\n| 2026 CapEx Guidance | **$175B–$185B** (midpoint $180B) |\n| Wall Street Expected | ~$116B |\n| 2025 CapEx | ~$91–93B |\n| 2024 CapEx | ~$52.5B |\n\n- ~2x YoY increase; rationale: AI infrastructure demand + supply constraints\n- **Q1 2026:** FX tailwind guided; depreciation growth to \"meaningfully increase\"; consensus revenue ~$103.9B\n- Other Bets losses to normalize (Q4 inflated by $2.1B Waymo charge)\n\n---\n\n### 8. Stock Price Reaction\n\n| Timeframe | Move |\n|-----------|------|\n| Initial after-hours | -7% |\n| During earnings call | Recovered to -2% |\n| Mid-call recovery | +2.4% intra-call |\n| Earnings day close | ~-2% |\n\nPrimary driver of sell-off: CapEx guidance $175–185B vs. consensus ~$116B (55%+ above expectations). Cloud beat and AI metrics partially offset the concern.\n\n---\n\n### 9. Key Analyst Takeaways\n\n- **Jefferies:** PT raised to $400; capex aggressive but \"the right action to take\"\n- **Broad consensus:** Bullish on Cloud trajectory (+48%) and AI execution; YouTube miss minor; capex debate will dominate 2026 narrative\n- **Sector read-through:** Broadcom +6% on Google's custom silicon/ASIC commitments; also positive for Celestica, Lumentum, TTM Technologies\n\n---\n\n**File target:** `analysis/research/alphabet_q4_2025_earnings.md` (write blocked by permission gate — data delivered inline for swarm capture)\n\nSources:\n- [CNBC — Alphabet Q4 2025 Earnings](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/04/alphabet-googl-q4-2025-earnings.html)\n- [SEC Filing — Q4 2025 Exhibit 99.1](https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1652044/000165204426000012/googexhibit991q42025.htm)\n- [Alphabet IR — Official Release](https://abc.xyz/investor/news/news-details/2026/Alphabet-Announces-Fourth-Quarter-2025-and-Fiscal-Year-Results-2026-KEvZIMKBLS/default.aspx)\n- [Motley Fool — Earnings Call Transcript](https://www.fool.com/earnings/call-transcripts/2026/02/04/alphabet-googl-q4-2025-earnings-call-transcript/)\n- [9to5Google — Q4 2025 Results](https://9to5google.com/2026/02/04/alphabet-q4-2025-earnings/)\n- [247WallSt — Live Coverage](https://247wallst.com/investing/2026/02/04/alphabet-live-complete-coverage-of-googs-q4-earnings/)\n- [Finviz — Cloud +48% / YouTube $60B](https://finviz.com/news/300252/alphabet-q4-highlights-google-cloud-revenue-up-48-youtube-tops-60-billion-for-2025)\n- [Neowin — $400B Milestone](https://www.neowin.net/news/alphabet-hits-400b-annual-revenue-milestone-as-google-cloud-surges-48/)\n- [Investing.com — Earnings Slides Analysis](https://www.investing.com/news/company-news/alphabet-q4-2025-slides-reveal-record-revenue-cloud-profitability-surge-93CH-4486304)" ;
