# === memory-8ef83c93-60b7-491a-b34d-36844043df51 ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:memory-8ef83c93-60b7-491a-b34d-36844043df51> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-28T14:53:36.716244Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Research company earnings\",\"Research Amazon Q4 2025 earnings\",\"researcher\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/tool_name> "researcher" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/structured_data> "null" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "c0e2c7eb-666e-4387-a65f-50891795fdf1" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "episodic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-28T14:53:36.715576+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "Write was blocked by the permission gate, same as the other research agents. Delivering findings as structured output for the swarm orchestrator:\n\n---\n\n## Amazon (AMZN) — Q4 2025 Earnings Research Findings\n\n**Reported:** February 5, 2026\n\n---\n\n### 1. Total Revenue & YoY Growth\n\n| Metric | Q4 2025 | Q4 2024 | YoY |\n|--------|---------|---------|-----|\n| Total Net Sales | $213.4B | $187.8B | +14% (+12% ex-FX) |\n| Operating Income | $25.0B | $21.2B | +18% |\n| Operating Margin | 11.7% | 11.3% | +40 bps |\n| Net Income | $21.2B | ~$20.0B | +6% |\n| Diluted EPS | $1.95 | $1.86 | +5% |\n\n**Full-year 2025:** Revenue $716.9B (+12% YoY); OCF $139.5B (+20% YoY)\n\n---\n\n### 2. EPS — Actual vs. Consensus\n\n| | EPS | Revenue |\n|-|-----|---------|\n| Actual | $1.95 | $213.4B |\n| Consensus | $1.97 | $211.5B |\n| Result | **MISS** (−$0.02) | **BEAT** (+$1.9B) |\n\n> EPS miss was narrow. Q4 included a ~$2.4B special charge (Amazon Leo / Kuiper satellites); adjusted OI ≈ $27.4B would have exceeded consensus.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Segment Revenue Breakdown\n\n| Segment | Revenue | YoY | Operating Income | Margin |\n|---------|---------|-----|-----------------|--------|\n| North America | $127.1B | +10% | $11.5B | 9.1% (+100 bps) |\n| International | $50.7B | +17% (+11% cc) | ~$3.0B | ~5.9% |\n| AWS | $35.6B | +24% | $12.47B | 35.0% |\n| **Total** | **$213.4B** | **+14%** | **$25.0B** | **11.7%** |\n\n---\n\n### 4. AWS Deep Dive\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| Revenue | $35.58B (+24% YoY) — fastest growth in 13 quarters |\n| Operating Income | $12.47B (beat consensus $11.91B) |\n| Operating Margin | 35.0% (vs. 34.6% Q3 2025; vs. 36.9% prior year) |\n| Annualized Run Rate | ~$142B |\n| Order Backlog | $244B (+40% YoY, +22% QoQ); avg. duration 4.1 years |\n| Custom Silicon Run Rate | >$10B (triple-digit YoY growth) |\n| Trainium2 | Fully sold out; Trainium3 largely committed by mid-2026 |\n| Amazon Bedrock ARR | Multi-billion; +60% QoQ spend growth |\n\n---\n\n### 5. Advertising Revenue\n\n| Metric | Q4 2025 | Q4 2024 | YoY |\n|--------|---------|---------|-----|\n| Advertising Services | $21.32B | $17.29B | +23% |\n| Full-Year 2025 | $68B+ | — | — |\n\n- Driven by Sponsored Products; Prime Video ads contributed \"meaningfully\"\n- Prime Video: ad-supported in 16 countries; avg. audience 315M viewers\n\n---\n\n### 6. E-commerce & Retail\n\n- North America margin 9.1% (+100 bps YoY) from delivery efficiency gains\n- Everyday Essentials: 1 in 3 US units, growing 2x faster than other categories\n- 8B+ items delivered same/next day in US (+30% YoY)\n- Amazon cited as lowest-price US retailer for 9th consecutive year\n\n---\n\n### 7. AI / Infrastructure CapEx\n\n| Year | CapEx |\n|------|-------|\n| 2025 (actual) | $128.3B |\n| 2026 (guidance) | ~$200B (+56% YoY) |\n| Analyst prior expectation | ~$146.6B |\n\n- \"Predominantly in AWS\" — data centers, Trainium/Graviton silicon, networking\n- Amazon Leo (Project Kuiper): 20+ satellite launches in 2026, 30+ in 2027\n\n---\n\n### 8. Forward Guidance — Q1 2026\n\n| Metric | Range | Consensus |\n|--------|-------|-----------|\n| Net Sales | $173.5B–$178.5B | $175.5B (in-line) |\n| Operating Income | $16.5B–$21.5B | $22.2B (**miss**) |\n\n- ~$1B YoY headwind from Amazon Leo in North America\n- ~180 bps favorable FX assumed\n\n---\n\n### 9. Stock Price Reaction\n\n| Event | Move |\n|-------|------|\n| After-hours Feb 5, 2026 | −11% |\n| Following session | −8% settled |\n| Primary driver | $200B capex vs. $146.6B expected; wide/low OI guidance |\n\nPart of broad \"CapEx panic\" across Big Tech. P/OCF compressed to 15.3x (near decade lows vs. 25x historical median).\n\n---\n\n### 10. Key Analyst Takeaways\n\n| Firm | PT Change | Rating |\n|------|-----------|--------|\n| Bank of America | $303 → $286 | Buy |\n| UBS | $310 → $311 | Buy |\n| Scotiabank | $275 → $300 | Outperform |\n\n**Bull:** AWS backlog $244B (+40%) = multi-year visibility; ads compounding at 23%; custom silicon >$10B; OCF at 15x is decade-low valuation.  \n**Bear:** FCF compressed to $11.2B in 2025 vs. $38B+ prior year; depreciation drag from $200B capex; Q1 OI guidance below consensus.\n\n---\n\n**Sources:**\n- [Amazon IR — Q4 2025 Press Release](https://ir.aboutamazon.com/news-release/news-release-details/2026/Amazon-com-Announces-Fourth-Quarter-Results/)\n- [CNBC — AMZN Q4 earnings report 2025](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/05/amazon-amzn-q4-earnings-report-2025.html)\n- [CNBC — AWS Q4 earnings report 2025](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/05/aws-q4-earnings-report-2025.html)\n- [Futurum — Amazon Q4 FY2025: AWS +24% Amid $200B CapEx Plan](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/amazon-q4-fy-2025-revenue-beat-aws-24-amid-200b-capex-plan/)\n- [Level-Headed Investing — Amazon Q4 2025 Earnings & 2026 Outlook](https://www.levelheadedinvesting.com/p/amazon-q4-2025-earnings-and-2026-outlook)\n- [Investing.com — Revenue jumps 14%, AWS +24%](https://www.investing.com/news/company-news/amazon-q4-2025-slides-revenue-jumps-14-aws-growth-accelerates-to-24-93CH-4489269)\n- [Marketing Dive — Amazon annual ad revenue passes $68B](https://www.marketingdive.com/news/amazon-annual-ad-revenue-passes-68b-boosted-by-full-funnel-strategy/811569/)\n- [Motley Fool — Amazon Q4 2025 Earnings Call Transcript](https://www.fool.com/earnings/call-transcripts/2026/02/05/amazon-amzn-q4-2025-earnings-call-transcript/)\n- [StockTwits — Amazon Q4 2025 Revenue Beats, $200B Capex](https://stocktwits.com/news-articles/markets/equity/amazon-q4-2025-revenue-beats-estimates-on-strong-aws-results-announces-200b-capital-spending-in-2026/cZbZl9hR4n3)\n- [Capital.com — Amazon Stock Forecast: Q4 2025 Results](https://capital.com/en-int/market-updates/amazon-stock-forecast-is-it-a-buy-24-02-2026)" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "98b1a881-21f5-4235-a198-d1939dbea76d" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Write was blocked by the permission gate, same as the other research agents. Delivering findings as structured output for the swarm orchestrator:\n\n---\n\n## Amazon (AMZN) — Q4 2025 Earnings Research Findings\n\n**Reported:** February 5, 2026\n\n---\n\n### 1. Total Revenue & YoY Growth\n\n| Metric | Q4 2025 | Q4 2024 | YoY |\n|--------|---------|---------|-----|\n| Total Net Sales | $213.4B | $187.8B | +14% (+12% ex-FX) |\n| Operating Income | $25.0B | $21.2B | +18% |\n| Operating Margin | 11.7% | 11.3% | +40 bps |\n| Net Income | $21.2B | ~$20.0B | +6% |\n| Diluted EPS | $1.95 | $1.86 | +5% |\n\n**Full-year 2025:** Revenue $716.9B (+12% YoY); OCF $139.5B (+20% YoY)\n\n---\n\n### 2. EPS — Actual vs. Consensus\n\n| | EPS | Revenue |\n|-|-----|---------|\n| Actual | $1.95 | $213.4B |\n| Consensus | $1.97 | $211.5B |\n| Result | **MISS** (−$0.02) | **BEAT** (+$1.9B) |\n\n> EPS miss was narrow. Q4 included a ~$2.4B special charge (Amazon Leo / Kuiper satellites); adjusted OI ≈ $27.4B would have exceeded consensus.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Segment Revenue Breakdown\n\n| Segment | Revenue | YoY | Operating Income | Margin |\n|---------|---------|-----|-----------------|--------|\n| North America | $127.1B | +10% | $11.5B | 9.1% (+100 bps) |\n| International | $50.7B | +17% (+11% cc) | ~$3.0B | ~5.9% |\n| AWS | $35.6B | +24% | $12.47B | 35.0% |\n| **Total** | **$213.4B** | **+14%** | **$25.0B** | **11.7%** |\n\n---\n\n### 4. AWS Deep Dive\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| Revenue | $35.58B (+24% YoY) — fastest growth in 13 quarters |\n| Operating Income | $12.47B (beat consensus $11.91B) |\n| Operating Margin | 35.0% (vs. 34.6% Q3 2025; vs. 36.9% prior year) |\n| Annualized Run Rate | ~$142B |\n| Order Backlog | $244B (+40% YoY, +22% QoQ); avg. duration 4.1 years |\n| Custom Silicon Run Rate | >$10B (triple-digit YoY growth) |\n| Trainium2 | Fully sold out; Trainium3 largely committed by mid-2026 |\n| Amazon Bedrock ARR | Multi-billion; +60% QoQ spend growth |\n\n---\n\n### 5. Advertising Revenue\n\n| Metric | Q4 2025 | Q4 2024 | YoY |\n|--------|---------|---------|-----|\n| Advertising Services | $21.32B | $17.29B | +23% |\n| Full-Year 2025 | $68B+ | — | — |\n\n- Driven by Sponsored Products; Prime Video ads contributed \"meaningfully\"\n- Prime Video: ad-supported in 16 countries; avg. audience 315M viewers\n\n---\n\n### 6. E-commerce & Retail\n\n- North America margin 9.1% (+100 bps YoY) from delivery efficiency gains\n- Everyday Essentials: 1 in 3 US units, growing 2x faster than other categories\n- 8B+ items delivered same/next day in US (+30% YoY)\n- Amazon cited as lowest-price US retailer for 9th consecutive year\n\n---\n\n### 7. AI / Infrastructure CapEx\n\n| Year | CapEx |\n|------|-------|\n| 2025 (actual) | $128.3B |\n| 2026 (guidance) | ~$200B (+56% YoY) |\n| Analyst prior expectation | ~$146.6B |\n\n- \"Predominantly in AWS\" — data centers, Trainium/Graviton silicon, networking\n- Amazon Leo (Project Kuiper): 20+ satellite launches in 2026, 30+ in 2027\n\n---\n\n### 8. Forward Guidance — Q1 2026\n\n| Metric | Range | Consensus |\n|--------|-------|-----------|\n| Net Sales | $173.5B–$178.5B | $175.5B (in-line) |\n| Operating Income | $16.5B–$21.5B | $22.2B (**miss**) |\n\n- ~$1B YoY headwind from Amazon Leo in North America\n- ~180 bps favorable FX assumed\n\n---\n\n### 9. Stock Price Reaction\n\n| Event | Move |\n|-------|------|\n| After-hours Feb 5, 2026 | −11% |\n| Following session | −8% settled |\n| Primary driver | $200B capex vs. $146.6B expected; wide/low OI guidance |\n\nPart of broad \"CapEx panic\" across Big Tech. P/OCF compressed to 15.3x (near decade lows vs. 25x historical median).\n\n---\n\n### 10. Key Analyst Takeaways\n\n| Firm | PT Change | Rating |\n|------|-----------|--------|\n| Bank of America | $303 → $286 | Buy |\n| UBS | $310 → $311 | Buy |\n| Scotiabank | $275 → $300 | Outperform |\n\n**Bull:** AWS backlog $244B (+40%) = multi-year visibility; ads compounding at 23%; custom silicon >$10B; OCF at 15x is decade-low valuation.  \n**Bear:** FCF compressed to $11.2B in 2025 vs. $38B+ prior year; depreciation drag from $200B capex; Q1 OI guidance below consensus.\n\n---\n\n**Sources:**\n- [Amazon IR — Q4 2025 Press Release](https://ir.aboutamazon.com/news-release/news-release-details/2026/Amazon-com-Announces-Fourth-Quarter-Results/)\n- [CNBC — AMZN Q4 earnings report 2025](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/05/amazon-amzn-q4-earnings-report-2025.html)\n- [CNBC — AWS Q4 earnings report 2025](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/05/aws-q4-earnings-report-2025.html)\n- [Futurum — Amazon Q4 FY2025: AWS +24% Amid $200B CapEx Plan](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/amazon-q4-fy-2025-revenue-beat-aws-24-amid-200b-capex-plan/)\n- [Level-Headed Investing — Amazon Q4 2025 Earnings & 2026 Outlook](https://www.levelheadedinvesting.com/p/amazon-q4-2025-earnings-and-2026-outlook)\n- [Investing.com — Revenue jumps 14%, AWS +24%](https://www.investing.com/news/company-news/amazon-q4-2025-slides-revenue-jumps-14-aws-growth-accelerates-to-24-93CH-4489269)\n- [Marketing Dive — Amazon annual ad revenue passes $68B](https://www.marketingdive.com/news/amazon-annual-ad-revenue-passes-68b-boosted-by-full-funnel-strategy/811569/)\n- [Motley Fool — Amazon Q4 2025 Earnings Call Transcript](https://www.fool.com/earnings/call-transcripts/2026/02/05/amazon-amzn-q4-2025-earnings-call-transcript/)\n- [StockTwits — Amazon Q4 2025 Revenue Beats, $200B Capex](https://stocktwits.com/news-articles/markets/equity/amazon-q4-2025-revenue-beats-estimates-on-strong-aws-results-announces-200b-capital-spending-in-2026/cZbZl9hR4n3)\n- [Capital.com — Amazon Stock Forecast: Q4 2025 Results](https://capital.com/en-int/market-updates/amazon-stock-forecast-is-it-a-buy-24-02-2026)" ;
