Revenue |\n|--------|-----|---------|\n| Greater China (incl. Taiwan, HK) | +37.9% | $25.53B |\n| Rest of Asia Pacific | +18.0% | — |\n| Europe | +12.7% | — |\n| Americas | +11.2% | — |\n| Japan | +4.7% | — |\n\n---\n\n### 5. Forward Guidance (Fiscal Q2 2026 / March Quarter)\n\n- Revenue growth: **+13–16% YoY**\n- Gross margin: **48–49%**\n- Operating expenses: **$18.4–18.7B**\n- Services growth: ~14% (similar to December quarter)\n- **Headwinds flagged:** Advanced-node supply constraints; memory cost pressure on Q2 gross margin\n\n*Source: Motley Fool earnings call transcript, MacRumors*\n\n---\n\n### 6. Management Commentary\n\n- **Tim Cook on iPhone:** \"The demand for iPhone was simply staggering, with revenue growing 23% year over year.\"\n- **On results overall:** Revenue \"well above our expectations\"; quarter described as \"record-breaking.\"\n- **On AI/Siri:** Announced Google collaboration on foundational models to power \"a more personalized Siri coming this year.\"\n- **On Greater China:** All-time revenue record; \"strong double-digit growth on switchers.\"\n- **Installed base:** 2.5B+ active devices. Shareholder returns: ~$32B; dividend $0.26/share payable Feb 12, 2026.\n\n*Source: Apple Newsroom, Motley Fool Q1 2026 transcript*\n\n---\n\n### 7. Stock Price Reaction\n\n| Period | Movement |\n|--------|---------|\n| After-hours Jan 29, 2026 | +2.0% to +2.9% |\n| Closing price ~earnings day | ~$261 |\n| YTD at earnings date | -6% |\n| YoY at earnings date | +14% |\n\n*Sources: [MarketBeat](https://www.marketbeat.com/stocks/NASDAQ/AAPL/forecast/), MacRumors, Yahoo Finance*\n\n---\n\n### 8. Key Analyst Takeaways\n\n| Firm | Action | Target | Rating |\n|------|--------|--------|--------|\n| JPMorgan | PT raised | $315 (from $305) | Overweight |\n| Citi (Atif Malik) | PT raised | $330 (from $315) | Buy |\n| TD Cowen | PT reiterated | $325 | — |\n| Consensus (77 analysts) | Bullish | $300 median ($215–$350) | — |\n\n**Themes:** iPhone 17 super-cycle beating expectations especially in China; Services validates high-margin model; AI/Siri + Google partnership is near-term catalyst; Mac/Wearables softness not concerning; Q2 supply constraints are primary watch item.\n\n*Sources: MarketBeat, Yahoo Finance analyst ratings, [TheStreet](https://www.thestreet.com/investing/morgan-stanley-resets-apple-stock-forecast-ahead-of-earnings), [Investing.com](https://www.investing.com/news/analyst-ratings/apple-stock-price-target-reiterated-at-325-by-td-cowen-on-ai-siri-outlook-93CH-4476519)*\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nApple's fiscal Q1 2026 (calendar Q4 2025, reported Jan 29, 2026) was a record-breaking quarter on virtually every metric. The iPhone 17 cycle drove a stunning 23% YoY iPhone revenue surge; Services crossed $30B for the first time; Greater China grew 38%. The company beat consensus EPS by 6.4% ($2.84 vs $2.67) and revenue by 3.8% ($143.8B vs $138.5B). Forward guidance of +13–16% revenue growth indicates momentum continues. Key risk flags: advanced-node supply constraints and memory cost headwinds may pressure Q2 gross margin slightly." ;
