# === memory-bb9e5bbb-b07d-43cb-866e-d76945b28c9d ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:memory-bb9e5bbb-b07d-43cb-866e-d76945b28c9d> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-28T14:43:49.393513Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Research sector impacts\",\"Research semiconductor sector impact\",\"researcher\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/tool_name> "researcher" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/structured_data> "null" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "c0e2c7eb-666e-4387-a65f-50891795fdf1" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "episodic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-28T14:43:49.392724+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "The write permission hasn't been granted, but here is the complete research output for the semiconductor sector:\n\n---\n\n## Semiconductor Sector: Q4 2025 Big Tech Earnings Impact\n\n### 1. Big Tech AI CapEx — The Core Demand Signal\n\nCollectively, the top-5 cloud/AI providers committed **$660–690 billion** in capex for 2026, up from ~$400B in 2025:\n\n| Company   | 2025 CapEx | 2026 Guidance | YoY Delta |\n|-----------|------------|---------------|-----------|\n| Amazon    | ~$125B     | ~$175B+       | ~+40%     |\n| Alphabet  | $91–93B    | $175–185B     | ~+95%     |\n| Microsoft | ~$94B (FY2026) | Accelerating | +45%+ |\n| Meta      | $70–72B    | $115–135B     | ~+70%     |\n\n**Alphabet's guidance alone more than doubled its 2025 outlay** — the single biggest capex expansion signal of the season.\n\nSources: [CNBC – Tech's $380B AI Splurge](https://www.cnbc.com/2025/10/31/tech-ai-google-meta-amazon-microsoft-spend.html) | [Futurum – AI Capex 2026: The $690B Sprint](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/ai-capex-2026-the-690b-infrastructure-sprint/)\n\n---\n\n### 2. SOX Index Performance: Jan–Feb 2026\n\n- **Early Jan 2026:** SOX hit record highs immediately, building on a **34.5% gain in 2025**.\n- **Peak (Feb 25, 2026):** SOX reached **8,498.10** — its highest-ever closing quote.\n- **VanEck SOXX ETF** rallied ~4% in early January, extending a ~49% 2025 run.\n- **WSTS** forecast a 26% jump in 2026 sector revenue to $975B; **BofA** (Vivek Arya) projected >$1 trillion (+30%).\n\nSources: [CNBC – Chip Stocks Rally to Start 2026](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/02/chipmakers-2026-ai-trade.html) | [Motley Fool – Semiconductor Spending to Hit $1 Trillion](https://www.fool.com/investing/2025/12/31/semiconductor-spending-is-set-to-hit-1-trillion-in/)\n\n---\n\n### 3. Key Semiconductor Stock Reactions\n\n**NVDA:**\n- Revenue +73% YoY, EPS +82% YoY — beat consensus handily\n- Data center revenue: $62B (+75% YoY, +22% QoQ)\n- Q1 FY2026 guidance: **$78B** vs. $72B consensus\n- Cited visibility to \"half a trillion dollars\" in Blackwell/Rubin revenue across 2026\n- Hyperscalers slightly >50% of data center revenue; diversification accelerating\n\nSource: [Motley Fool – NVDA Q4 Earnings Beat](https://www.fool.com/investing/2026/02/25/nvda-stock-earnings-q4-guidance-ai-stocks/)\n\n**AMD:**\n- Q4 revenue: $10.27B — beat $9.67B consensus\n- Full-year 2025 data center revenue: Record $16.6B (+32% YoY)\n- **Stock dropped ~17%** — weak Q1 guidance disappointed; still 11x smaller than NVDA in data center\n\nSource: [CNBC – AMD Stock Sinks 17%](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/04/amd-stock-earnings-forecast-chips.html)\n\n**AVGO (Broadcom):**\n- Q4 FY2025: Revenue $18.02B (beat); adj. EPS $1.95 (beat)\n- AI semiconductor revenue +74% YoY; full-year AI revenue $20B (+65% YoY)\n- Guided AI chip sales to **double to $8.2B** in Q1 FY2026\n- **Dropped ~15%** post-earnings on profit-taking despite record results\n- 5th hyperscaler custom XPU customer acquired; Anthropic confirmed with $10B+ order\n\nSources: [CNBC – Broadcom Beats, AI Chip Sales to Double](https://www.cnbc.com/2025/12/11/broadcom-avgo-q4-earnings-2025.html) | [Yahoo Finance – AVGO Q4 Highlights](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/broadcom-inc-avgo-q4-2025-050036753.html)\n\n**TSMC:**\n- Q4 2025: Revenue $33.73B (+25.5% YoY); full-year $122.42B — historic highs\n- Gross margin: **62.3%** — all-time record, beat guidance of 59–61%\n- HPC = 55% of revenue; AI accelerators at high-teens % of total\n- CoWoS still supply-constrained (15–20% gap); capacity to expand **69% in 2026**\n- Monthly CoWoS capacity target raised to ~127,000 wafers\n\nSources: [FinancialContent – TSMC Q4 AI Boom](https://markets.financialcontent.com/stocks/article/marketminute-2026-1-19-taiwan-semiconductor-tsm-q4-2025-earnings-ai-boom-drives-historic-2026-outlook) | [Futurum – TSMC FY2025 Results](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/tsmc-q4-fy-2025-results-and-fy-2026-outlook-signal-ai-led-growth/)\n\n**ASML:**\n- Q4 2025 bookings: **€13.2B** vs. €6.32B expected — **more than 2x consensus**\n- Split: €7.4B EUV + €5.8B non-EUV\n- **Surged 7%** on results day (Jan 28, 2026)\n- 2026 guidance: €34–39B revenue\n- China revenue falling from 33% to 20% of sales (export control headwind)\n\nSources: [CNBC – ASML Surges 7% on Record AI Orders](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/28/asml-q4-2025-earnings-report.html) | [Globe and Mail – ASML Lifts 2026 Outlook](https://www.theglobeandmail.com/investing/article-asml-fourth-quarter-results-2026-outlook-ai-chip-orders-job-cuts/)\n\n---\n\n### 4. Supply Chain Signals\n\n**TSMC Utilization:**\n- Full utilization on N3/N5; nearly every major AI accelerator (NVDA Rubin, Google TPU v7/v8, Amazon Trainium3, AMD MI350X) moving to N3 simultaneously\n- AI wafers ~60% of N3 output in 2026; projected to hit **86% by 2027**\n\n**HBM Demand:**\n- Micron can only meet **55–60% of core customer demand**\n- SK Hynix and Samsung raised HBM3E prices **~20%** for 2026 contracts\n- SK Hynix reportedly **sole HBM3E supplier** for Microsoft's Maia 200 chip (TSMC 3nm, announced Jan 27, 2026)\n\n**Custom Silicon Acceleration:**\n\n| Hyperscaler | Chip | Node | Status |\n|-------------|------|------|--------|\n| Google | TPU v6e (Trillium) | TSMC | 100,000+ chip GA; 90K wafer/mo reserved |\n| Amazon | Trainium3 | TSMC 3nm | Full deployment early 2026; used by Anthropic, OpenAI |\n| Microsoft | Maia 200 | TSMC 3nm | Announced Jan 2026 |\n\nCustom silicon is a headwind to NVDA/AMD share but a tailwind for TSMC and AVGO (as the XPU design partner).\n\nSources: [The Decoder – AI Chips Pushing Off TSMC Lines](https://the-decoder.com/ai-chips-are-pushing-everything-else-off-tsmcs-most-advanced-production-lines/) | [TrendForce – Maia 200 / HBM3E](https://www.trendforce.com/news/2026/01/27/news-microsoft-unveils-maia-200-ai-chip-on-tsmc-3nm-sk-hynix-reportedly-sole-hbm3e-supplier/) | [Nerd Level Tech – Custom AI Chip Race 2026](https://nerdleveltech.com/the-custom-ai-chip-race-2026-meta-google-amazon-microsoft-vs-nvidia)\n\n---\n\n### 5. Earnings Surprise Table\n\n| Stock | Surprise | Move |\n|-------|----------|------|\n| ASML | Bookings 2x consensus | **+7%** |\n| Teradyne | Revenue +43.9% YoY, beat by 11% | **+21.9%** |\n| Marvell | Revenue +22.1% YoY | **+18.5%** |\n| NVDA | $78B guidance vs. $72B consensus | **Strong +** |\n| TSMC | Record revenue + margin beat | **Positive** |\n| AMD | Revenue beat, weak Q1 guidance | **-17%** |\n| AVGO | Beat but priced for perfection | **-15%** |\n| Intel | Cautious foundry outlook | **Underperformer** |\n\n---\n\n### 6. Sector Causation Summary\n\n```\nBig Tech Q4 2025 Earnings (Jan-Feb 2026)\n          |\n          v\nAI CapEx: $660-690B aggregate for 2026\n          |\n   .------+-------.-----------.-------------------.\n   v              v           v                   v\n NVDA/AMD      TSMC/foundry  Equipment         HBM/Memory\n SOX record    Record        Record bookings   +20% pricing\n highs         margins       (ASML 2x est.)    power\n```\n\n- **SOX peak:** 8,498.10 on Feb 25, 2026\n- **Primary driver:** Hyperscaler capex commitments confirm a multi-year AI infrastructure cycle with no demand pullback\n- **Binding constraint:** CoWoS advanced packaging and HBM supply are the tightest supply bottlenecks through 2026\n- **Share-loss risk:** Custom silicon erodes NVDA/AMD % share, but expands absolute TSMC and AVGO TAM\n- **Equipment play:** Record ASML bookings signal a new capex upcycle — bullish for LRCX, AMAT, KLAC" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "55393e20-1184-43b5-bd3d-f50f41872602" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The write permission hasn't been granted, but here is the complete research output for the semiconductor sector:\n\n---\n\n## Semiconductor Sector: Q4 2025 Big Tech Earnings Impact\n\n### 1. Big Tech AI CapEx — The Core Demand Signal\n\nCollectively, the top-5 cloud/AI providers committed **$660–690 billion** in capex for 2026, up from ~$400B in 2025:\n\n| Company   | 2025 CapEx | 2026 Guidance | YoY Delta |\n|-----------|------------|---------------|-----------|\n| Amazon    | ~$125B     | ~$175B+       | ~+40%     |\n| Alphabet  | $91–93B    | $175–185B     | ~+95%     |\n| Microsoft | ~$94B (FY2026) | Accelerating | +45%+ |\n| Meta      | $70–72B    | $115–135B     | ~+70%     |\n\n**Alphabet's guidance alone more than doubled its 2025 outlay** — the single biggest capex expansion signal of the season.\n\nSources: [CNBC – Tech's $380B AI Splurge](https://www.cnbc.com/2025/10/31/tech-ai-google-meta-amazon-microsoft-spend.html) | [Futurum – AI Capex 2026: The $690B Sprint](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/ai-capex-2026-the-690b-infrastructure-sprint/)\n\n---\n\n### 2. SOX Index Performance: Jan–Feb 2026\n\n- **Early Jan 2026:** SOX hit record highs immediately, building on a **34.5% gain in 2025**.\n- **Peak (Feb 25, 2026):** SOX reached **8,498.10** — its highest-ever closing quote.\n- **VanEck SOXX ETF** rallied ~4% in early January, extending a ~49% 2025 run.\n- **WSTS** forecast a 26% jump in 2026 sector revenue to $975B; **BofA** (Vivek Arya) projected >$1 trillion (+30%).\n\nSources: [CNBC – Chip Stocks Rally to Start 2026](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/02/chipmakers-2026-ai-trade.html) | [Motley Fool – Semiconductor Spending to Hit $1 Trillion](https://www.fool.com/investing/2025/12/31/semiconductor-spending-is-set-to-hit-1-trillion-in/)\n\n---\n\n### 3. Key Semiconductor Stock Reactions\n\n**NVDA:**\n- Revenue +73% YoY, EPS +82% YoY — beat consensus handily\n- Data center revenue: $62B (+75% YoY, +22% QoQ)\n- Q1 FY2026 guidance: **$78B** vs. $72B consensus\n- Cited visibility to \"half a trillion dollars\" in Blackwell/Rubin revenue across 2026\n- Hyperscalers slightly >50% of data center revenue; diversification accelerating\n\nSource: [Motley Fool – NVDA Q4 Earnings Beat](https://www.fool.com/investing/2026/02/25/nvda-stock-earnings-q4-guidance-ai-stocks/)\n\n**AMD:**\n- Q4 revenue: $10.27B — beat $9.67B consensus\n- Full-year 2025 data center revenue: Record $16.6B (+32% YoY)\n- **Stock dropped ~17%** — weak Q1 guidance disappointed; still 11x smaller than NVDA in data center\n\nSource: [CNBC – AMD Stock Sinks 17%](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/04/amd-stock-earnings-forecast-chips.html)\n\n**AVGO (Broadcom):**\n- Q4 FY2025: Revenue $18.02B (beat); adj. EPS $1.95 (beat)\n- AI semiconductor revenue +74% YoY; full-year AI revenue $20B (+65% YoY)\n- Guided AI chip sales to **double to $8.2B** in Q1 FY2026\n- **Dropped ~15%** post-earnings on profit-taking despite record results\n- 5th hyperscaler custom XPU customer acquired; Anthropic confirmed with $10B+ order\n\nSources: [CNBC – Broadcom Beats, AI Chip Sales to Double](https://www.cnbc.com/2025/12/11/broadcom-avgo-q4-earnings-2025.html) | [Yahoo Finance – AVGO Q4 Highlights](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/broadcom-inc-avgo-q4-2025-050036753.html)\n\n**TSMC:**\n- Q4 2025: Revenue $33.73B (+25.5% YoY); full-year $122.42B — historic highs\n- Gross margin: **62.3%** — all-time record, beat guidance of 59–61%\n- HPC = 55% of revenue; AI accelerators at high-teens % of total\n- CoWoS still supply-constrained (15–20% gap); capacity to expand **69% in 2026**\n- Monthly CoWoS capacity target raised to ~127,000 wafers\n\nSources: [FinancialContent – TSMC Q4 AI Boom](https://markets.financialcontent.com/stocks/article/marketminute-2026-1-19-taiwan-semiconductor-tsm-q4-2025-earnings-ai-boom-drives-historic-2026-outlook) | [Futurum – TSMC FY2025 Results](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/tsmc-q4-fy-2025-results-and-fy-2026-outlook-signal-ai-led-growth/)\n\n**ASML:**\n- Q4 2025 bookings: **€13.2B** vs. €6.32B expected — **more than 2x consensus**\n- Split: €7.4B EUV + €5.8B non-EUV\n- **Surged 7%** on results day (Jan 28, 2026)\n- 2026 guidance: €34–39B revenue\n- China revenue falling from 33% to 20% of sales (export control headwind)\n\nSources: [CNBC – ASML Surges 7% on Record AI Orders](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/28/asml-q4-2025-earnings-report.html) | [Globe and Mail – ASML Lifts 2026 Outlook](https://www.theglobeandmail.com/investing/article-asml-fourth-quarter-results-2026-outlook-ai-chip-orders-job-cuts/)\n\n---\n\n### 4. Supply Chain Signals\n\n**TSMC Utilization:**\n- Full utilization on N3/N5; nearly every major AI accelerator (NVDA Rubin, Google TPU v7/v8, Amazon Trainium3, AMD MI350X) moving to N3 simultaneously\n- AI wafers ~60% of N3 output in 2026; projected to hit **86% by 2027**\n\n**HBM Demand:**\n- Micron can only meet **55–60% of core customer demand**\n- SK Hynix and Samsung raised HBM3E prices **~20%** for 2026 contracts\n- SK Hynix reportedly **sole HBM3E supplier** for Microsoft's Maia 200 chip (TSMC 3nm, announced Jan 27, 2026)\n\n**Custom Silicon Acceleration:**\n\n| Hyperscaler | Chip | Node | Status |\n|-------------|------|------|--------|\n| Google | TPU v6e (Trillium) | TSMC | 100,000+ chip GA; 90K wafer/mo reserved |\n| Amazon | Trainium3 | TSMC 3nm | Full deployment early 2026; used by Anthropic, OpenAI |\n| Microsoft | Maia 200 | TSMC 3nm | Announced Jan 2026 |\n\nCustom silicon is a headwind to NVDA/AMD share but a tailwind for TSMC and AVGO (as the XPU design partner).\n\nSources: [The Decoder – AI Chips Pushing Off TSMC Lines](https://the-decoder.com/ai-chips-are-pushing-everything-else-off-tsmcs-most-advanced-production-lines/) | [TrendForce – Maia 200 / HBM3E](https://www.trendforce.com/news/2026/01/27/news-microsoft-unveils-maia-200-ai-chip-on-tsmc-3nm-sk-hynix-reportedly-sole-hbm3e-supplier/) | [Nerd Level Tech – Custom AI Chip Race 2026](https://nerdleveltech.com/the-custom-ai-chip-race-2026-meta-google-amazon-microsoft-vs-nvidia)\n\n---\n\n### 5. Earnings Surprise Table\n\n| Stock | Surprise | Move |\n|-------|----------|------|\n| ASML | Bookings 2x consensus | **+7%** |\n| Teradyne | Revenue +43.9% YoY, beat by 11% | **+21.9%** |\n| Marvell | Revenue +22.1% YoY | **+18.5%** |\n| NVDA | $78B guidance vs. $72B consensus | **Strong +** |\n| TSMC | Record revenue + margin beat | **Positive** |\n| AMD | Revenue beat, weak Q1 guidance | **-17%** |\n| AVGO | Beat but priced for perfection | **-15%** |\n| Intel | Cautious foundry outlook | **Underperformer** |\n\n---\n\n### 6. Sector Causation Summary\n\n```\nBig Tech Q4 2025 Earnings (Jan-Feb 2026)\n          |\n          v\nAI CapEx: $660-690B aggregate for 2026\n          |\n   .------+-------.-----------.-------------------.\n   v              v           v                   v\n NVDA/AMD      TSMC/foundry  Equipment         HBM/Memory\n SOX record    Record        Record bookings   +20% pricing\n highs         margins       (ASML 2x est.)    power\n```\n\n- **SOX peak:** 8,498.10 on Feb 25, 2026\n- **Primary driver:** Hyperscaler capex commitments confirm a multi-year AI infrastructure cycle with no demand pullback\n- **Binding constraint:** CoWoS advanced packaging and HBM supply are the tightest supply bottlenecks through 2026\n- **Share-loss risk:** Custom silicon erodes NVDA/AMD % share, but expands absolute TSMC and AVGO TAM\n- **Equipment play:** Record ASML bookings signal a new capex upcycle — bullish for LRCX, AMAT, KLAC" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "[researcher] The write permission hasn't been granted, but here is the complete research outp" ;
	a <https://schema.org/EpisodicMemory> .


