# === memory-ff21adc4-ccbe-496a-97d0-121495c4edeb ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:memory-ff21adc4-ccbe-496a-97d0-121495c4edeb> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-28T14:48:33.95535Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Research company earnings\",\"Research Microsoft Q4 2025 earnings\",\"researcher\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/tool_name> "researcher" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/structured_data> "null" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "c0e2c7eb-666e-4387-a65f-50891795fdf1" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "episodic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-28T14:48:33.954690+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "File writes are gated by the permission system in this context. Delivering complete research findings as structured output:\n\n---\n\n## Microsoft Q4 2025 Earnings Research — FINDINGS\n\n**File target:** `analysis/research/microsoft_q4_2025_earnings.md`\n\n---\n\n### 1. Total Revenue & YoY Growth\n\n| Metric | Value | YoY |\n|--------|-------|-----|\n| Total Revenue | $81.3B | +17% (+15% cc) |\n| Operating Income | $38.3B | +21% (+19% cc) |\n| Net Income (GAAP) | $38.5B | +60% |\n| Net Income (non-GAAP) | $30.9B | +23% (+21% cc) |\n| Operating Margin | 47% | — |\n| CapEx (Q2) | $37.5B | — |\n\n> GAAP net income +60% reflects a one-time gain (likely equity investment revaluation); non-GAAP +23% is the operating measure.\n\n*Sources: [Microsoft Source](https://news.microsoft.com/source/2026/01/28/microsoft-cloud-and-ai-strength-drives-second-quarter-results-3/), [Futurum](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/microsoft-q2-fy-2026-cloud-surpasses-50b-azure-up-38-cc/)*\n\n---\n\n### 2. EPS — Actual vs. Consensus\n\n| | non-GAAP EPS | GAAP EPS | Revenue |\n|-|-------------|----------|---------|\n| Actual | $4.14 | $5.16 | $81.27B |\n| Consensus | ~$3.85–$3.97 (LSEG: $3.97) | — | ~$80.3B |\n| Beat | +$0.17–$0.29 (+7%) | — | +$1.0B (+1.2%) |\n\n*Sources: [Yahoo Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/microsoft-q2-earnings-beat-estimates-155700958.html), [247WallSt](https://247wallst.com/companies/msft/earnings)*\n\n---\n\n### 3. Segment Revenue Breakdown\n\n| Segment | Revenue | YoY | Notes |\n|---------|---------|-----|-------|\n| Productivity & Business Processes | $34.1B | +16% | M365 Commercial Cloud +17%; LinkedIn +11%; Dynamics 365 +19% |\n| Intelligent Cloud | $32.9B | +29% | Azure +39%; beat StreetAccount est. $32.46B |\n| More Personal Computing | $14.3B | -3% | Windows, Xbox, Search drag |\n| **Microsoft Cloud Total** | **$51.5B** | **+26%** | **First time ever exceeding $50B quarterly** |\n\n*Sources: [Microsoft IR](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/Investor/earnings/FY-2026-Q2/performance), [Futurum](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/microsoft-q2-fy-2026-cloud-surpasses-50b-azure-up-38-cc/)*\n\n---\n\n### 4. Azure Growth & Cloud Commentary\n\n- **Azure & Other Cloud Services:** +39% YoY (+38% constant currency); decelerated 1 ppt from Q1's +40%\n- **Commercial RPO:** $625B (+110% YoY); ~45% driven by OpenAI commitments\n- **Cloud gross margin:** ~67% (down YoY due to AI infrastructure investment)\n- CFO Amy Hood: *\"If all new GPUs had been allocated exclusively to Azure, growth would have been well above 39%\"* — demand exceeds supply\n\n*Sources: [Fortune](https://fortune.com/2026/01/28/microsoft-stock-drops-azure-growth-slows-capex-spending-q2/), [Futurum](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/microsoft-q2-fy-2026-cloud-surpasses-50b-azure-up-38-cc/)*\n\n---\n\n### 5. AI / Copilot Adoption Metrics\n\n| Product | Metric | Value | YoY/QoQ |\n|---------|--------|-------|---------|\n| M365 Copilot | Paid seats | 15 million | +160% YoY |\n| M365 Copilot | Daily active users | — | +10x YoY |\n| M365 Copilot | Conversations/user | — | 2x YoY |\n| M365 Copilot | 35,000+ seat deployments | — | 3x YoY |\n| GitHub Copilot | Paid subscribers | 4.7 million | +75% YoY |\n| GitHub Copilot Pro Plus | — | — | +77% QoQ |\n| Azure AI Foundry | Active customers | 1,500+ | — |\n| Azure AI Foundry | $1M+/qtr spenders | — | +80% YoY |\n| Azure AI Foundry | 1T+ tokens/yr on track | 250+ customers | — |\n| Microsoft Fabric | ARR | >$2.0B | — |\n| Microsoft Fabric | Customer count | 31,000+ | +60% YoY |\n\nCEO Satya Nadella: *\"We are only at the beginning phases of AI diffusion and already Microsoft has built an AI business that is larger than some of our biggest franchises.\"*\n\n*Sources: [Futurum](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/microsoft-q2-fy-2026-cloud-surpasses-50b-azure-up-38-cc/), [Microsoft Source](https://news.microsoft.com/source/2026/01/28/microsoft-cloud-and-ai-strength-drives-second-quarter-results-3/)*\n\n---\n\n### 6. Forward Guidance\n\n| Item | Guidance |\n|------|----------|\n| Q3 FY2026 Revenue | $80.65B–$81.75B (+15–17% YoY) |\n| Q3 Azure growth (cc) | 37–38% (slight sequential deceleration) |\n| H1 FY2026 CapEx total | ~$72.4B ($34.9B Q1 + $37.5B Q2) |\n| Q2 Shareholder Returns | $12.7B (+32% YoY) |\n\nCFO Amy Hood: *\"We exceeded expectations across revenue, operating income, and earnings per share.\"*\n\n*Sources: [Futurum](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/microsoft-q2-fy-2026-cloud-surpasses-50b-azure-up-38-cc/), [CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/28/microsoft-msft-q2-earnings-report-2026.html)*\n\n---\n\n### 7. Stock Price Reaction\n\n| Period | Move | Notes |\n|--------|------|-------|\n| After-hours Jan 28 | -5% to -7% | Beat on EPS and revenue, punished on guidance |\n| Following weeks | ~-15% to -17% from highs | Sector-wide tech selloff compounded post-earnings decline |\n\n**Root cause of selloff:** Azure Q3 guidance ~1 ppt below buy-side expectations; $37.5B/quarter CapEx rising faster than revenue.\n\nMorgan Stanley (Keith Weiss): *\"Capex is growing faster than we expected, and maybe Azure is growing a little bit slower than we expected.\"*\n\n*Sources: [Fortune](https://fortune.com/2026/01/28/microsoft-stock-drops-azure-growth-slows-capex-spending-q2/), [Yahoo Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/analysts-cut-microsoft-msft-price-115534415.html)*\n\n---\n\n### 8. Analyst Takeaways\n\n| Firm | Action | New PT | Old PT | Rating |\n|------|--------|--------|--------|--------|\n| Raymond James | Cut PT | $580 | $600 | Outperform |\n| Piper Sandler | Cut PT | $600 | $650 | Overweight |\n| Scotiabank | Cut PT | $600 | $650 | — |\n| TD Cowen | Cut PT | $610 | $625 | — |\n| JPMorgan | Cut PT | $550 | $575 | — |\n| Consensus (34 analysts) | — | $598 median | — | Mostly Buy |\n\n**Bear:** CapEx/revenue ratio widening; Azure deceleration trend; RPO inflated by OpenAI commitments.  \n**Bull:** AI at scale (15M Copilot seats, 4.7M GitHub Copilot); $625B RPO = multi-year visibility; capacity-constrained implies upside as supply catches up.\n\n*Sources: [Yahoo Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/analysts-cut-microsoft-msft-price-115534415.html), [MarketBeat](https://www.marketbeat.com/stocks/NASDAQ/MSFT/forecast/)*\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nMicrosoft's fiscal Q2 2026 (calendar Q4 2025) was a classic **beat-and-drop**. Beat on revenue (+$1B), non-GAAP EPS (+7%), and all three segments. Microsoft Cloud crossed $50B/quarter for the first time. Azure grew 39% and AI adoption metrics were explosive. But the stock fell 5–7% after-hours because: (1) Azure Q3 guidance missed buy-side by ~1 ppt, (2) $37.5B/quarter CapEx raised ROI concerns, and (3) $625B RPO was partially OpenAI-driven. The AI monetization thesis is intact; the debate is about how fast supply constraints resolve into accelerating Azure growth.\n\n---\n\n**Sources:**\n- [Microsoft Source – Official Press Release](https://news.microsoft.com/source/2026/01/28/microsoft-cloud-and-ai-strength-drives-second-quarter-results-3/)\n- [Futurum – Cloud Surpasses $50B; Azure Up 38% CC](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/microsoft-q2-fy-2026-cloud-surpasses-50b-azure-up-38-cc/)\n- [CNBC – MSFT Q2 Earnings Report 2026](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/28/microsoft-msft-q2-earnings-report-2026.html)\n- [Fortune – Stock Drops, Azure Growth Slows](https://fortune.com/2026/01/28/microsoft-stock-drops-azure-growth-slows-capex-spending-q2/)\n- [Yahoo Finance – Microsoft Q2 Earnings Beat Estimates](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/microsoft-q2-earnings-beat-estimates-155700958.html)\n- [Yahoo Finance – Analysts Cut MSFT Price Targets](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/analysts-cut-microsoft-msft-price-115534415.html)\n- [247WallSt – MSFT Earnings Beat/EPS/Revenue](https://247wallst.com/companies/msft/earnings)\n- [MarketBeat – MSFT Forecast & Analyst Targets](https://www.marketbeat.com/stocks/NASDAQ/MSFT/forecast/)\n- [Microsoft IR – FY26 Q2 Performance](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/Investor/earnings/FY-2026-Q2/performance)" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "75d4f74e-015b-4f7d-926a-8f21d417e34f" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "File writes are gated by the permission system in this context. Delivering complete research findings as structured output:\n\n---\n\n## Microsoft Q4 2025 Earnings Research — FINDINGS\n\n**File target:** `analysis/research/microsoft_q4_2025_earnings.md`\n\n---\n\n### 1. Total Revenue & YoY Growth\n\n| Metric | Value | YoY |\n|--------|-------|-----|\n| Total Revenue | $81.3B | +17% (+15% cc) |\n| Operating Income | $38.3B | +21% (+19% cc) |\n| Net Income (GAAP) | $38.5B | +60% |\n| Net Income (non-GAAP) | $30.9B | +23% (+21% cc) |\n| Operating Margin | 47% | — |\n| CapEx (Q2) | $37.5B | — |\n\n> GAAP net income +60% reflects a one-time gain (likely equity investment revaluation); non-GAAP +23% is the operating measure.\n\n*Sources: [Microsoft Source](https://news.microsoft.com/source/2026/01/28/microsoft-cloud-and-ai-strength-drives-second-quarter-results-3/), [Futurum](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/microsoft-q2-fy-2026-cloud-surpasses-50b-azure-up-38-cc/)*\n\n---\n\n### 2. EPS — Actual vs. Consensus\n\n| | non-GAAP EPS | GAAP EPS | Revenue |\n|-|-------------|----------|---------|\n| Actual | $4.14 | $5.16 | $81.27B |\n| Consensus | ~$3.85–$3.97 (LSEG: $3.97) | — | ~$80.3B |\n| Beat | +$0.17–$0.29 (+7%) | — | +$1.0B (+1.2%) |\n\n*Sources: [Yahoo Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/microsoft-q2-earnings-beat-estimates-155700958.html), [247WallSt](https://247wallst.com/companies/msft/earnings)*\n\n---\n\n### 3. Segment Revenue Breakdown\n\n| Segment | Revenue | YoY | Notes |\n|---------|---------|-----|-------|\n| Productivity & Business Processes | $34.1B | +16% | M365 Commercial Cloud +17%; LinkedIn +11%; Dynamics 365 +19% |\n| Intelligent Cloud | $32.9B | +29% | Azure +39%; beat StreetAccount est. $32.46B |\n| More Personal Computing | $14.3B | -3% | Windows, Xbox, Search drag |\n| **Microsoft Cloud Total** | **$51.5B** | **+26%** | **First time ever exceeding $50B quarterly** |\n\n*Sources: [Microsoft IR](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/Investor/earnings/FY-2026-Q2/performance), [Futurum](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/microsoft-q2-fy-2026-cloud-surpasses-50b-azure-up-38-cc/)*\n\n---\n\n### 4. Azure Growth & Cloud Commentary\n\n- **Azure & Other Cloud Services:** +39% YoY (+38% constant currency); decelerated 1 ppt from Q1's +40%\n- **Commercial RPO:** $625B (+110% YoY); ~45% driven by OpenAI commitments\n- **Cloud gross margin:** ~67% (down YoY due to AI infrastructure investment)\n- CFO Amy Hood: *\"If all new GPUs had been allocated exclusively to Azure, growth would have been well above 39%\"* — demand exceeds supply\n\n*Sources: [Fortune](https://fortune.com/2026/01/28/microsoft-stock-drops-azure-growth-slows-capex-spending-q2/), [Futurum](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/microsoft-q2-fy-2026-cloud-surpasses-50b-azure-up-38-cc/)*\n\n---\n\n### 5. AI / Copilot Adoption Metrics\n\n| Product | Metric | Value | YoY/QoQ |\n|---------|--------|-------|---------|\n| M365 Copilot | Paid seats | 15 million | +160% YoY |\n| M365 Copilot | Daily active users | — | +10x YoY |\n| M365 Copilot | Conversations/user | — | 2x YoY |\n| M365 Copilot | 35,000+ seat deployments | — | 3x YoY |\n| GitHub Copilot | Paid subscribers | 4.7 million | +75% YoY |\n| GitHub Copilot Pro Plus | — | — | +77% QoQ |\n| Azure AI Foundry | Active customers | 1,500+ | — |\n| Azure AI Foundry | $1M+/qtr spenders | — | +80% YoY |\n| Azure AI Foundry | 1T+ tokens/yr on track | 250+ customers | — |\n| Microsoft Fabric | ARR | >$2.0B | — |\n| Microsoft Fabric | Customer count | 31,000+ | +60% YoY |\n\nCEO Satya Nadella: *\"We are only at the beginning phases of AI diffusion and already Microsoft has built an AI business that is larger than some of our biggest franchises.\"*\n\n*Sources: [Futurum](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/microsoft-q2-fy-2026-cloud-surpasses-50b-azure-up-38-cc/), [Microsoft Source](https://news.microsoft.com/source/2026/01/28/microsoft-cloud-and-ai-strength-drives-second-quarter-results-3/)*\n\n---\n\n### 6. Forward Guidance\n\n| Item | Guidance |\n|------|----------|\n| Q3 FY2026 Revenue | $80.65B–$81.75B (+15–17% YoY) |\n| Q3 Azure growth (cc) | 37–38% (slight sequential deceleration) |\n| H1 FY2026 CapEx total | ~$72.4B ($34.9B Q1 + $37.5B Q2) |\n| Q2 Shareholder Returns | $12.7B (+32% YoY) |\n\nCFO Amy Hood: *\"We exceeded expectations across revenue, operating income, and earnings per share.\"*\n\n*Sources: [Futurum](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/microsoft-q2-fy-2026-cloud-surpasses-50b-azure-up-38-cc/), [CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/28/microsoft-msft-q2-earnings-report-2026.html)*\n\n---\n\n### 7. Stock Price Reaction\n\n| Period | Move | Notes |\n|--------|------|-------|\n| After-hours Jan 28 | -5% to -7% | Beat on EPS and revenue, punished on guidance |\n| Following weeks | ~-15% to -17% from highs | Sector-wide tech selloff compounded post-earnings decline |\n\n**Root cause of selloff:** Azure Q3 guidance ~1 ppt below buy-side expectations; $37.5B/quarter CapEx rising faster than revenue.\n\nMorgan Stanley (Keith Weiss): *\"Capex is growing faster than we expected, and maybe Azure is growing a little bit slower than we expected.\"*\n\n*Sources: [Fortune](https://fortune.com/2026/01/28/microsoft-stock-drops-azure-growth-slows-capex-spending-q2/), [Yahoo Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/analysts-cut-microsoft-msft-price-115534415.html)*\n\n---\n\n### 8. Analyst Takeaways\n\n| Firm | Action | New PT | Old PT | Rating |\n|------|--------|--------|--------|--------|\n| Raymond James | Cut PT | $580 | $600 | Outperform |\n| Piper Sandler | Cut PT | $600 | $650 | Overweight |\n| Scotiabank | Cut PT | $600 | $650 | — |\n| TD Cowen | Cut PT | $610 | $625 | — |\n| JPMorgan | Cut PT | $550 | $575 | — |\n| Consensus (34 analysts) | — | $598 median | — | Mostly Buy |\n\n**Bear:** CapEx/revenue ratio widening; Azure deceleration trend; RPO inflated by OpenAI commitments.  \n**Bull:** AI at scale (15M Copilot seats, 4.7M GitHub Copilot); $625B RPO = multi-year visibility; capacity-constrained implies upside as supply catches up.\n\n*Sources: [Yahoo Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/analysts-cut-microsoft-msft-price-115534415.html), [MarketBeat](https://www.marketbeat.com/stocks/NASDAQ/MSFT/forecast/)*\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nMicrosoft's fiscal Q2 2026 (calendar Q4 2025) was a classic **beat-and-drop**. Beat on revenue (+$1B), non-GAAP EPS (+7%), and all three segments. Microsoft Cloud crossed $50B/quarter for the first time. Azure grew 39% and AI adoption metrics were explosive. But the stock fell 5–7% after-hours because: (1) Azure Q3 guidance missed buy-side by ~1 ppt, (2) $37.5B/quarter CapEx raised ROI concerns, and (3) $625B RPO was partially OpenAI-driven. The AI monetization thesis is intact; the debate is about how fast supply constraints resolve into accelerating Azure growth.\n\n---\n\n**Sources:**\n- [Microsoft Source – Official Press Release](https://news.microsoft.com/source/2026/01/28/microsoft-cloud-and-ai-strength-drives-second-quarter-results-3/)\n- [Futurum – Cloud Surpasses $50B; Azure Up 38% CC](https://futurumgroup.com/insights/microsoft-q2-fy-2026-cloud-surpasses-50b-azure-up-38-cc/)\n- [CNBC – MSFT Q2 Earnings Report 2026](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/28/microsoft-msft-q2-earnings-report-2026.html)\n- [Fortune – Stock Drops, Azure Growth Slows](https://fortune.com/2026/01/28/microsoft-stock-drops-azure-growth-slows-capex-spending-q2/)\n- [Yahoo Finance – Microsoft Q2 Earnings Beat Estimates](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/microsoft-q2-earnings-beat-estimates-155700958.html)\n- [Yahoo Finance – Analysts Cut MSFT Price Targets](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/analysts-cut-microsoft-msft-price-115534415.html)\n- [247WallSt – MSFT Earnings Beat/EPS/Revenue](https://247wallst.com/companies/msft/earnings)\n- [MarketBeat – MSFT Forecast & Analyst Targets](https://www.marketbeat.com/stocks/NASDAQ/MSFT/forecast/)\n- [Microsoft IR – FY26 Q2 Performance](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/Investor/earnings/FY-2026-Q2/performance)" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "[researcher] File writes are gated by the permission system in this context. Delivering compl" ;
	a <https://schema.org/EpisodicMemory> .


